# Content Modules Guide

Content modules are shortcodes that help structure and enhance article content.

## Section Header Module

Location: [layouts/shortcodes/content-modules/section-header.html](mdc:layouts/shortcodes/content-modules/section-header.html)

Creates visually distinct section headers with optional icons and badges.

```hugo
{{< content-modules/section-header title="Section Title" level="2" icon="ðŸ“·" badge="Expert Guide" >}}
  Section description goes here.
{{< /content-modules/section-header >}}
```

Parameters:
- `title`: Header text (required)
- `level`: Heading level - "2", "3", or "4" (default: "2")
- `icon`: Optional icon to display
- `badge`: Optional badge text
- `id`: Custom ID for direct linking (default: slug of title)

## FAQ Module

Location: [layouts/shortcodes/content-modules/faq.html](mdc:layouts/shortcodes/content-modules/faq.html)

Displays expandable question/answer pairs with schema.org markup.

```hugo
{{< content-modules/faq title="Common Questions" id="faq-section" >}}
  {{< content-modules/faq-item question="Question text?" open="true" >}}
    Answer text goes here.
  {{< /content-modules/faq-item >}}
  
  {{< content-modules/faq-item question="Another question?" >}}
    Another answer.
  {{< /content-modules/faq-item >}}
{{< /content-modules/faq >}}
```

Parameters for faq:
- `title`: Heading for the FAQ section (default: "Frequently Asked Questions")
- `id`: Custom ID for the section (default: "faq-section")
- `schema`: Whether to include schema.org markup (default: "true")

Parameters for faq-item:
- `question`: Question text (required)
- `open`: Whether the item should be initially expanded (default: "false")
